Biker reacts lightning fast and prevents worse
On Friday evening, a traffic accident occurred on the highway between Machtolsheim and Merklingen, in which a motorcyclist was only slightly injured thanks to his rapid reaction.
Car driver overlooks biker
A 44-year-old driver wanted to turn left with her VW from Merklingen onto Landesstraße 1230 in the direction of Machtolsheim at around 9.30 p.m.
She overlooked the 24-year-old motorcyclist coming from Nellingen.
Hand and foot brake levers fly away in the collision
The biker tried to avoid the car, but still grabbed it at the rear of the vehicle.
Due to the stripping process, the hand and foot brake levers on the Suzuki were torn off and the driver was no longer able to brake.
At present, he steered his motorcycle in the green stiffnesses next to the road and let it roll out there without falling.
Biker suffers leg injury
Due to the collision with the car, the biker suffered an injury to Beim and had to be treated in a clinic.
Mamming: Corona Mass Infection: 174 Harvester Infected
After a Corona mass infection on a large vegetable farm in Mamming, Lower Bavaria, almost 500 people are under quarantine and are no longer allowed to leave the company.
A security service monitors the ban.
A total of 174 harvesters were tested positive for the Corona pathogen Sars-CoV-2 during the series examination, as the district office Dingolfing-Landau announced on Saturday evening.
"In order to avoid further expansion, we unfortunately have to take this step to protect the population," explained District Administrator Werner Bumeder (CSU).
Previously, seven employees had already become infected in the company - this was the occasion of the series test.
The farm is a large vegetable farm that grows strawberries, cucumbers, cabbage and beetroot - but the cucumbers only for pickling glasses.
Mamming is a rural municipality with a good 3,300 inhabitants not far from Dingolfing with its large BMW plant.
Bumeder appealed to the citizens to keep calm: "According to our information it is a closed group of people".
On the farm infected were separated from uninfected employees, the site is now surrounded by a barrier fence.
The Greens and the SPD shared responsibility for the state government.
The two opposition factions accused Prime Minister Markus Söder (CSU) and his cabinet of neglecting the control of seasonal workers.
"This can take bitter revenge if such local infection events have to be reached out and regional lockdowns have to be ordered," said Jürgen Mistol, the parliamentary managing director of the Greens.
The SPD sees this quite similarly: "After the Corona outbreak in the Wiesenhof slaughterhouse in mid-May, we have already called for a special control programme for farms with harvesters," said environmental expert Florian von Brunn.
"In our view, the hygiene conditions at the workplace and the living conditions need to be closely monitored.
This obviously did not happen. "
The outbreak came "with announcement".
Underground station Aidenbachstraße: Dangerous dispute: 19-year-old falls into the track bed after Schubser
In a dispute between two youth groups at Aidenbachstraße underground station, a 19-year-old fell through a thrust and slipped into the track bed.
Obersendling - On Friday there was a dispute between two youth groups at the underground station Aidenbachstraße around 4.15 pm.
A passer-by alerted the police, who approached with several stripes.
According to the first investigation, a Munich (17) pushed a 19-year-old to the ground.
The young man slipped over the edge of the platform and fell into the track bed.
People from the 17-year-old group helped the fallen man climb out of the track.
There was no danger of an entering railway.
According to the police, there were clashes between the two people.
The 17-year-old fled the scene, but his personal details could be determined in retrospect.
Accompanied by his father, he went to Police Inspectorate 29.
The 17-year-old is investigated for assault.
Report: Seehofer urges longer data retention
Data retention is currently suspended.
According to a media report, however, Federal Minister of the Interior Horst Seehofer calls for an extension of the storage period.
He wants to strengthen the fight against child abuse.
According to a media report, Federal Minister of the Interior Horst Seehofer (CSU) calls for extended data retention - instead of the planned ten weeks for half a year.
As the "Bild am Sonntag" reports, Seehofer Minister of Justice Christine Lambrecht (SPD) asked in a letter for a quick change of law.
Seehofer therefore wants to strengthen the measures against child abuse.
He considers it sensible "to make urgently needed adjustments to the law already now", quotes the newspaper from the letter.
Data retention is currently suspended.
A decision by the ECJ is expected to do so.
Seehofer, however, wants the amendments beforehand so that they could be applied immediately after a possible positive ruling, the report continues.
A spokesman for the Ministry of Justice told the newspaper that it could only be sensibly examined whether legal adjustments were required if the courts had decided.
In the fight against child abuse and child pornography, Seehofer, together with the interior ministers of the states, had already spoken out in June in favour of data retention.
