Clearing of Frankfurter Opernplatz run peacefully
One week after the riots in Frankfurt, the evacuation of Opernplatz took place peacefully in the night after Sunday.
Finally, several dozen people stayed on the square, but left it at 1 a.m.
The police have been deployed with numerous officers since the early evening, and there has been a large police force throughout the city.
For the first time this weekend from midnight, there was a ban on entry to the Opera Square, where there had been riots a week ago.
Police officers had been attacked with bottles from the crowd of the celebrants.
