Car flips over: Young woman seriously injured in accident on federal highway 83 at Hofgeismar
In an accident between Schöneberg and Hümme, a 21-year-old suffered serious injuries on Sunday at around 1.25 p.m.
She was taken to the Klinikum Kassel.
With thermal imaging cameras, the fire brigade searched for possible passengers.
According to the police, the woman was on Bundesstraße 83 in the direction of her place of residence Hümme, when her car came off the road for hitherto unexplained cause and flipped over several times.
In order to save the accidents, the fire brigade had to cut free the roof of the car.
Since it was unclear whether there was anyone else in the vehicle, the adjacent corn field was searched from the turntable ladder with a thermal imaging camera.
The drone squadron from Warburg, which also works with thermal imaging cameras, had also been ordered for the search for people.
However, the volunteers found no one between the tall corn plants.
The seriously injured man was taken to the Kassel hospital for further care with the ambulance.
Almost 50 firefighters from the Hofgeismar, Hümme and Schöneberg fire brigade were on site.
The highway was closed for two hours due to the accident.
